'''Dave Cockrum''' was a [[Star Wars comic books|comic-book]] artist who worked for both [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] and [[Wikipedia:DC Comics|DC Comics]]. Cockrum's first work in the comic industry after leaving the United States Navy was for [[Wikipedia:Warren Publishing|Warren Publishing]], and he was later hired by DC Comics to draw [[Wikipedia:Legion of Superheroes|''Legion of Superheroes'']] stories. In [[1975]] Cockrum joined Marvel Comics, where he and writer [[Len Wein]] revived the [[Wikipedia:X-Men|''X-Men'']] comic series adding several new characters of their own creation including [[Wikipedia:Storm (comics)|Storm]], [[Wikipedia:Colossus (comics)|Colossus]], and (Cockrum's favorite) [[Wikipedia:Nightcrawler (comics)|Nightcrawler]].

